title: Coalition Split Could See More Support for One Nation | 10 News+
description: One Nation stands set to benefit the most as right-leaning voters become disillusioned. Barnaby Joyce told 10 News Plus it’s almost as if his former Coalition colleagues are recruiting for his new party. title: Manhunt Underway After Three People Killed In NSW Country Town | 10 News
description: Three people have been killed and another man seriously injured after a gunman opened fire in country New South Wales, in what's believed to be a domestic violence attack. It happened in the town of Lake Cargelligo more than 450 kilometres away from Sydney – where locals are being told to stay indoors tonight. description: Donald Trump has unveiled his “Board of Peace” and will soon meet with Ukraine's Volodymyr Zelenskyy on the sidelines of the Davos summit. title: Musk Jokes About "Piece" Deal At Davos | 10 News
description: Elon Musk has used an appearance at the World Economic Forum in Switzerland to joke that a "peace" deal meant a "piece of Greenland," and a "piece of Venezuela."  In an on-stage appearance, Musk joked that "peace" was actually spelled "p-i-e-c-e," and referenced Donald Trump's ongoing campaign to expand US sovereign territory into Greenland and Venezuela.  Musk also repeated frequent talking points about his vision of a world with "billions" of humanoid robots that would take over the role of child rearing and pet minding from humans. title: JD Vance Defends ICE Detaining 5-Year-Old Boy In Minneapolis | 10 News
description: JD Vance has defended the administration’s immigration crackdown in Minnesota and the recent taking of a child by ICE.  School officials claim US Immigration and Customs Enforcement detained a five-year-old boy in Minnesota on Tuesday as he returned home from school and transported him and his father to a Texas detention centre.  Vance pushed back against claims that the boy was arrested and defended ICE agents stating, “Well, what are they supposed to do? Are they supposed to let a five-year-old child freeze to death?”  The Vice President is currently visiting Minneapolis in an attempt to “tone down the temperature a little bit, reduce the chaos, but still allow us as a federal government to enforce the American immigration laws”. title: Cyclone Harry Causes Over 1 Billion Euros Worth Of Damage Across Southern Italy | 10 News
description: Authorities have stated the damage from Cyclone Harry has climbed over 1 billion euros across southern Italy, as destructive winds and storm surges battered coastlines.  Sicily and Sardinia were hit the hardest by the storm, with regional leaders reporting hundreds of millions of euros in losses to roads, harbours, beachfront facilities and productive activities.  Footage released by the Italian Coast Guard shows extensive damage along ports and coastlines, with storm surges battering quays, vessels and seaside infrastructure.
